reviews.review_text:
Fine dining Restaurent near miramer beach, Goa specialising in local goan cuisine . Great ambience,attentive service and good food. The red boiled rice served to us was undercooked - except that all dishes were spot on and the quantity is also big enough for two to share
A small garden in front makes you feel that you are not in the city but in a quiet remote place
Good place for the local cuisine

We visited this place after it was highly recommended. We ordered prawns and poi was given free. It tasted pretty good with authentic Goan taste. We loved the rice and King fish curry.

When we went on a Friday afternoon, it was completely empty. Although we had taken a reservation via phone. Staff were friendly and ambience was good. Food was a bit expensive which we realised only after spending couple of days in Goa.

Definitely visit once for the Ambience, hospitality and the food taste.

I would say food is good. But I personally dint find it Wow as per so many reviews. I would rate the food 7/10.

Anything except main course is a very small quantity for the price. A bit disappointed with all the hype and the result. Please do come here but not with a super big expectation in terms of taste or ambience.

I made a reservation online which was for 600. When I walked in, it was empty. So I do understand there is a lot of fomo going on about this place but don't be overwhelmed when you call on customer care and they say it's only by reservations. You can simply walk in too.
